headline: Icotrokinra delivered an industry-leading combination of significant skin clearance with demonstrated tolerability in a once daily pill in Phase 3 topline results
summary: Johnson & Johnson (NYSE: JNJ) today announced positive topline results from ICONIC-LEADa, a pivotal Phase 3 investigational study of icotrokinra (JNJ-2113), the first targeted oral peptide that selectively blocks the IL-23 receptor, in adults and adolescents 12 years of age and older with moderate to severe plaque psoriasis (PsO). The Phase 3 study met its co-primary endpoints of Psoriasis Area and Severity Index (PASI) 90b and Investigator's Global Assessment (IGA) of 0/1c response at week 16 a
